# Git Command Reference Guide

A comprehensive guide to commonly used Git commands.

---

## Basic Commands
1. **`git status`**: Show the state of your working directory.
2. **`git diff`**: Show file differences not yet staged.
3. **`git add <file_path>`**: Add file(s) to the staging area.
4. **`git commit -a -m "commit message"`**: Commit all tracked changes with a message.
5. **`git commit --amend`**: Modify the last commit.

---

## Branching and Merging
6. **`git branch`**: Lists branches.
7. **`git branch -D <branch_name>`**: Delete a branch forcefully.
8. **`git branch --set-upstream-to <remote_branch>`**: Set the upstream branch.
9. **`git checkout -b <branch_name>`**: Create and switch to a new branch.
10. **`git checkout <branch_name>`**: Switch to an existing branch.
11. **`git merge <branch_name>`**: Merge branches together.

---

## Remote Repositories
12. **`git clone <repository_url>`**: Create a local copy of a remote repository.
13. **`git push origin <branch_name>`**: Push a branch to a remote.
14. **`git pull`**: Fetch and merge remote changes.
15. **`git fetch`**: Fetch changes from the remote repository without merging.

---

## Resetting and Reverting
16. **`git reset`**: Undo commits by moving branch reference.
17. **`git reset HEAD~1`**: Undo the last commit, preserving changes locally.
18. **`git reset --soft HEAD^`**: Undo the last commit, but keep the changes.
19. **`git reset --hard <commit>`**: Resets everything to a previous commit, erasing all uncommitted changes.
20. **`git revert <commit_id>`**: Create a new commit that undoes the changes of a specific commit.

---

## Rebasing and Cherry-Picking
21. **`git rebase <branch_name>`**: Rebase the current branch onto another branch.
22. **`git rebase -i`**: Rebase interactively and rewrite commit history.
23. **`git cherry-pick <commit_id>`**: Apply changes from a specific commit.

---

## Stashing
24. **`git stash`**: Stash changes for later.
25. **`git stash pop`**: Apply and remove stashed changes.

---

## Viewing and Logging
26. **`git log --stat`**: Show commit logs with stats.
27. **`git show <commit_id>`**: Show details about a specific commit.

---

## Advanced Usage
28. **`git checkout <commit>`**: Switch the working directory to a specific commit.
29. **`git reset --soft HEAD^`**: Undo the last commit, but keep the changes staged.
30. **`git reset --hard HEAD~1`**: Completely reset to the previous commit.

---

Keep this guide handy for quick reference while working with Git!
